		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Brownian motion</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<dl>
<dd><i>This article is about the physical phenomenon; for the stochastic process, see <a href="/wiki/Wiener_process" title="Wiener process">Wiener process</a>. For the sports team, see <a href="/wiki/Brownian_Motion_(Ultimate)" title="Brownian Motion (Ultimate)" class="mw-redirect">Brownian Motion (Ultimate)</a>. For the mobility model, see <a href="/wiki/Random_walk" title="Random walk">Random walk</a>.</i></dd>
</dl>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Brownian_hierarchical.svg" class="image" title="Three different views of Brownian motion, with 32 steps, 256 steps, and 2048 steps denoted by progressively lighter colors."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Brownian_hierarchical.svg/180px-Brownian_hierarchical.svg.png" width="180" height="188" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Brownian_hierarchical.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
